signal-desktop (Signal for Desktop)

Signal is an encrypted instant messaging and voice calling application
for Android, iOS, and the desktop. It uses the Internet to send
one-to-one and group messages, which can include images and video
messages, and make one-to-one voice/video calls.

This is a repackaging of the official binary .deb file distributed by
Open Whipser Systems.

Local customizations
--------------------
This SlackBuild patches Signal's bundled app.asar to add:

  - Multiple font profiles. Each profile rewrites Signal's "Inter" font
    family at the CSS @font-face level to point at a system-installed
    font via local(). Original (vanilla) asar is always preserved as
    app.asar.orig and is selectable.
  - 5% Ctrl+= / Ctrl+- zoom step (Signal's default is ~20% per press).
    Ctrl+0 still resets to 100%.

Build dependencies for the asar repack:
  - nodejs (provides node + npx)
    First build needs network access; npx fetches @electron/asar.

Optional build variable:
  FONT_PROFILE=<name>   Default profile installed as app.asar on first
                        install (or after upgradepkg if no prior choice
                        exists).
                        Default: helveticaneue
                        Available: dejavu, frutiger, futura, helveticaneue,
                                   notosans, optima, ubuntu, univers
                        plus 'orig' (vanilla Signal, always built).

  Example:  FONT_PROFILE=notosans ./signal-desktop.SlackBuild

The active profile name is recorded in /opt/Signal/resources/.active-profile.
On upgradepkg, doinst.sh reads this file and re-installs the previously
selected profile, preserving the user's choice.

Profiles assume the matching system fonts are installed:
  helveticaneue, univers, optima, frutiger, futura  - Linotype TTFs
  notosans, ubuntu, dejavu                          - typically already
                                                      present on Slackware

Switching profile after install
-------------------------------
A `signal-font` helper is installed to /usr/bin. Switching copies the
chosen variant over /opt/Signal/resources/app.asar; root is required.

  signal-font                    # list profiles, show active
  sudo signal-font ubuntu        # switch to Ubuntu
  sudo signal-font orig          # revert to upstream Signal
  signal-font -h                 # help

Profile changes do not take effect until Signal is restarted.
